{"info": {"author": "Zerynth Team", "author_email": "d.neri@zerynth.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# Zerynth ZDM Client Python Library\n\nA python library that emulates a device for the  ZDM (Zerynth Device Maanager).\nThe library permits: to connect to the ZDM, to send data and to receive jobs.\n\n## Installation\n\nThe latest stable version [is available on PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/zdm-client-py/). Either add `zdm-client-py` to your `requirements.txt` file or install with pip:\n```\npip install zdm-client-py\n```\n\n## Usage\nLogin to the ZDM platform (by using the [ZDM Cloud](https://zdm.zerynth.com) or the [ZDM Cli](https://docs.zerynth.com/latest/)).\nAdd a new device and generate a new password for the device.\n\nCopy the obtained **Device Id** and **Password** in the example below.\n\nIn the example, the Client connects to the ZDM with the username e password.\nThen it sends an infinite stream of messages onto three different tags (\"bathroom\", \"bedroom\", \"living room\") with a random temperature.\n\n```python\nimport random\nimport time\nimport zdm\n\ndevice_id = '!!! PUT YOU DEVICE_ID HERE !!!'\npassword = '!!! PUT YOU PASSWORD HER !!!'\n\ndevice = zdm.ZDMClient(device_id=device_id)\ndevice.set_password(password)\ndevice.connect()\n\ntime.sleep(5)\n\ntags = [\"tag1\", \"tag2\", \"tag3\"]\n\nwhile True:\n    temp = random.randint(10, 30)  # random temperature\n    tag = random.choice(tags)      # random choice of the tag\n    payload = {\"temp\": temp}\n    device.publish_data(tag, payload)\n    time.sleep(1)\n```\n\nYou can find other examples in the `data/examples` folder.\n\n=======\nHistory\n=======\n\n0.0.11 (2020-05-04)\n----------------------------\n* fix json load arguments of job\n\n0.0.10 (2020-04-27)\n----------------------------\n* Changed default endpoint to \"mqtt.zdm.zerynth.com\"\n* Fix args of Jobs as ./json\n\n\n0.0.7 (2020-04-09)\n----------------------------\n* modified examples\n* copy examples in /usr/share/zdm/examples folder\n\n0.0.6 (2020-03-30)\n----------------------------\n\n* Fix error in _handle_dn_msg decode msg to str with python3.5\n\n\n0.0.5 (2020-03-29)\n----------------------------\n\n* Fix error manifest with empty jobs.\n\n\n0.0.4 (2020-03-29)\n----------------------------\nNew functionality:\n\n* Verbose parameter to ZdmClient class\n\n\n0.0.3 (2020-03-27)\n----------------------------\nRelease with support Python >3\n\n* Create ZDmClient\n* Publish messages to ZDM\n* Received Jobs from ZDM\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/zerynth/zdm-client-py.git", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "zdm-client-py", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/zdm-client-py/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/zdm-client-py/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/zerynth/zdm-client-py.git"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/zdm-client-py/0.0.11/", "requires_dist": ["paho-mqtt", "click"], "requires_python": ">=3", "summary": "ZDM Client Python Library", "version": "0.0.11", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Zerynth ZDM Client Python Library</h1>\n<p>A python library that emulates a device for the  ZDM (Zerynth Device Maanager).\nThe library permits: to connect to the ZDM, to send data and to receive jobs.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>The latest stable version <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/zdm-client-py/\" rel=\"nofollow\">is available on PyPI</a>. Either add <code>zdm-client-py</code> to your <code>requirements.txt</code> file or install with pip:</p>\n<pre><code>pip install zdm-client-py\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>Login to the ZDM platform (by using the <a href=\"https://zdm.zerynth.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">ZDM Cloud</a> or the <a href=\"https://docs.zerynth.com/latest/\" rel=\"nofollow\">ZDM Cli</a>).\nAdd a new device and generate a new password for the device.</p>\n<p>Copy the obtained <strong>Device Id</strong> and <strong>Password</strong> in the example below.</p>\n<p>In the example, the Client connects to the ZDM with the username e password.\nThen it sends an infinite stream of messages onto three different tags (\"bathroom\", \"bedroom\", \"living room\") with a random temperature.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">random</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">time</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">zdm</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">device_id</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'!!! PUT YOU DEVICE_ID HERE !!!'</span>\n<span class=\"n\">password</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'!!! PUT YOU PASSWORD HER !!!'</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">device</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">zdm</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ZDMClient</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">device_id</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">device_id</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set_password</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">password</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">connect</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">time</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sleep</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">tags</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">\"tag1\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"tag2\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"tag3\"</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">while</span> <span class=\"kc\">True</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">temp</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">random</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">randint</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>  <span class=\"c1\"># random temperature</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">tag</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">random</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">choice</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">tags</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>      <span class=\"c1\"># random choice of the tag</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">payload</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"s2\">\"temp\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">temp</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">publish_data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">tag</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">payload</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">time</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sleep</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>You can find other examples in the <code>data/examples</code> folder.</p>\n<h1>=======\nHistory</h1>\n<h2>0.0.11 (2020-05-04)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>fix json load arguments of job</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>0.0.10 (2020-04-27)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Changed default endpoint to \"mqtt.zdm.zerynth.com\"</li>\n<li>Fix args of Jobs as ./json</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>0.0.7 (2020-04-09)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>modified examples</li>\n<li>copy examples in /usr/share/zdm/examples folder</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>0.0.6 (2020-03-30)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix error in _handle_dn_msg decode msg to str with python3.5</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>0.0.5 (2020-03-29)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix error manifest with empty jobs.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>0.0.4 (2020-03-29)</h2>\n<p>New functionality:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Verbose parameter to ZdmClient class</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>0.0.3 (2020-03-27)</h2>\n<p>Release with support Python &gt;3</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create ZDmClient</li>\n<li>Publish messages to ZDM</li>\n<li>Received Jobs from ZDM</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7165350, "releases": {"0.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "27a1a1628c6bbde4c79687438fae16c3", "sha256": "65398c438147b59fc18516baa38db0b4b8ad7f0b31acd9579f12313156a4a2b4"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "zdm_client_py-0.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "27a1a1628c6bbde4c79687438fae16c3", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 7114, "upload_time": "2020-03-25T21:25:28", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-25T21:25:28.915330Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/48/d9/1c9e996c68a463122404cdbc55558d0e2ebc521f8131b295a53c995de254/zdm_client_py-0.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}], "0.0.10": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "26b0471c57d65d2229592196be959278", "sha256": "771e6df9c5633b4cf34b003f24d73481cc79ebbbb01b3bedebb021e2d7b6143e"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "zdm_client_py-0.0.10-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "26b0471c57d65d2229592196be959278", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3", "size": 8655, "upload_time": "2020-04-27T12:07:06", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-27T12:07:06.676521Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/45/bd/812252498e29b4771d823a2489891abb5ea8d26d55931d41979e93bee6c7/zdm_client_py-0.0.10-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}], "0.0.11": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "cf56382666ecbba01efa762bc2c8accb", "sha256": "7b9455c6d9db0659b39dce594448790d4f55862cc93407a0c18c05137982a44c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "zdm_client_py-0.0.11-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_diges